SIMPLE: tournament
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tournament
<hw>Tour"na*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>turnement</ets>, <ets>tornement</ets>, OF. <ets>torneiement</ets>,
<ets>tornoiement</ets>, F. <ets>tournoiement</ets> a turning or wheeling
round. See <er>Tourney</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A mock fight, or
warlike game, formerly in great favor, in which a number of combatants
were engaged, as an exhibition of their address and bravery; hence,
figuratively, a real battle.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In battle and in
<xex>tourneyment</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With cruel <qex>tournament</qex> the squadrons join.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It different from the <xex>joust</xex>, which was a
trial of skill between one man and another.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any contest of skill in which there are many
contestents for championship; <as>as, a chess
<ex>tournament</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tournery</ent>⟦br⟧
